From: Peter Zijlstra <peterz@infradead.org>
Date: Mon, 27 Jun 2022 22:21:17 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] x86/retbleed: Add fine grained Kconfig knobs
Patch-mainline: 5.18.14
References: CVE-2022-29900 CVE-2022-29901 bsc#1012628 bsc#1199657
Git-commit: f43b9876e857c739d407bc56df288b0ebe1a9164

commit f43b9876e857c739d407bc56df288b0ebe1a9164 upstream.

Do fine-grained Kconfig for all the various retbleed parts.

NOTE: if your compiler doesn't support return thunks this will
silently 'upgrade' your mitigation to IBPB, you might not like this.

Signed-off-by: Peter Zijlstra (Intel) <peterz@infradead.org>
